N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 16 ยง 233.1 - Definitions

State Regulations
(a) Dwelling. A
building designed or used as the living unit for one or more families. For the
purposes of this standard, mobile homes shall not be considered
dwellings. (b) Historical building. Any building or structure designated historically significant by the State or
local governing body, or listed (or determined by the Secretary of the Interior
to be eligible to be listed) in The National Register of Historic

Places. Notes
